“It was a massacre because of the right to vote,” he said.
“The murders had a clear subtext for all black locals: ‘This is how you get if you register and go to vote.’”
The annual reconstruction of the Moore's Ford Bridge is organized by Cassandra Greene for almost a decade.
Her performance is figurative, captivating and elaborate, showing deep-seated racism that many would like to consider extinct in modern America.
