A Pladis spokeswoman said: “The Tollcross construction manager received a letter from GMB only yesterday and the company will issue a statement as soon as possible, as we appreciate the continued commitment to employees and trade union representatives.
A regular meeting with GMB employees and representatives at Tollcross took place two months ago and many issues were openly discussed at this meeting.
We talked to employees that, as in all companies operating in extremely competitive and uncertain economic conditions, we evaluate our operations on a regular basis, which applies to all our operations, so that we can continue to successfully compete with others.
She added: “In recent years, we have invested <0xC2><0xA3>5 million in Tollcross, particularly in production lines and operational efficiencies.
We greatly appreciate the heritage of Tollcross and the local area, and in the event of any changes to the operation of the factory, employees and trade union representatives will be informed immediately."
